#: ../../../policy/CMP0213.rst:2
msgid "CMP0213"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../policy/CMP0213.rst:6
msgid ""
":command:`file(ARCHIVE_CREATE)` and :command:`file(ARCHIVE_EXTRACT)` encode "
"archive paths as UTF-8 by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../policy/CMP0213.rst:9
msgid ""
"CMake 4.3 and below always used the ``OEM`` (current locale) encoding for "
"archive paths.  CMake 4.4 offer the ``ENCODING`` option, but prefer to use "
"``UTF-8`` by default.  This policy provides compatibility for projects that "
"have not been updated to specify the encoding or accept the new default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../policy/CMP0213.rst:14
msgid ""
"The ``OLD`` behavior for this policy is to use the current locale as the "
"default encoding, which is also known as an ``OEM`` encoding. The ``NEW`` "
"behavior uses ``UTF-8`` as the default encoding."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../policy/include/STANDARD_ADVICE.rst:1
msgid ""
"This policy was introduced in CMake version |INTRODUCED_IN_CMAKE_VERSION|. "
"It may be set by :command:`cmake_policy` or :command:"
"`cmake_minimum_required`. If it is not set, CMake |WARNS_OR_DOES_NOT_WARN|, "
"and uses ``OLD`` behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../policy/include/DEPRECATED.rst:2
msgid ""
"The ``OLD`` behavior of a policy is :ref:`deprecated by definition <cmake-"
"policies-intro>` and may be removed in a future version of CMake."
msgstr ""
